## Limitations

The findings presented in this report are based on a limited number of studies and articles, which may not capture the full range of experiences and outcomes associated with social media detoxes. Additionally, the effectiveness of a social media cleanse can be highly individualistic, influenced by personal habits, the extent of social media use, and psychological factors. Further research is needed to explore long-term effects and to identify which populations may benefit most from such interventions.